programs.name: BSc International Business Administration
programs.description: The BSc International Business Administration at Tilburg University prepares students to become international business professionals. The program focuses on all functional aspects of business and integrates socially oriented courses, providing the necessary professional and practical skills for a managerial career in a global environment.

programs.name: BSc Entrepreneurship and Business Innovation
programs.description: The BSc Entrepreneurship and Business Innovation at Tilburg University is designed for students eager to create new value through entrepreneurship and business innovation. The program provides a solid academic foundation in entrepreneurship, business innovation, economics, finance, law, and ethics, combining academic insights with hands-on training.

programs.name: LLB Global Law
programs.description: The LLB Global Law at Tilburg University offers a comprehensive legal education with a global perspective. The program covers various legal systems and cultures, preparing students for a career in international law and global governance.

programs.name: BSc Psychology
programs.description: The BSc Psychology program at Tilburg University provides a comprehensive understanding of human behavior and mental processes. The program covers various psychological theories and practices, preparing students for diverse careers in psychology and related fields.

programs.name: BSc Cognitive Science and Artificial Intelligence
programs.description: The BSc Cognitive Science and Artificial Intelligence at Tilburg University combines insights from cognitive science and artificial intelligence to understand and develop intelligent systems. The program focuses on the intersection of human cognition and AI technologies, preparing students for careers in AI development, data science, and cognitive research.

programs.name: BSc Economics
programs.description: The BSc Economics program at Tilburg University provides a thorough understanding of economic principles and their application in real-world scenarios. The program covers microeconomics, macroeconomics, and econometrics, preparing students for careers in economic analysis, policy advising, and financial consulting.

programs.name: BA Liberal Arts and Sciences
programs.description: The BA Liberal Arts and Sciences program at Tilburg University offers a broad and interdisciplinary education, allowing students to explore various fields such as humanities, social sciences, and natural sciences. The program emphasizes critical thinking, creativity, and global awareness, preparing students for diverse career paths.

programs.name: BSc Data Science
programs.description: The BSc Data Science program at Tilburg University equips students with the skills to analyze and interpret complex data. The program combines computer science, statistics, and domain knowledge to prepare students for careers in data analysis, machine learning, and data-driven decision-making.

programs.name: BSc Econometrics and Operations Research
programs.description: The BSc Econometrics and Operations Research program at Tilburg University combines mathematics, statistics, and computer science to solve complex economic and business challenges. It prepares students for careers in data-driven decision-making, quantitative analysis, and operations optimization across various industries.

programs.name: BSc Global Management of Social Issues
programs.description: The BSc Global Management of Social Issues at Tilburg University prepares students to tackle complex societal challenges through the integration of management, sociology, and psychology. The program focuses on global issues such as poverty, migration, climate change, and inequality, equipping students with interdisciplinary knowledge and practical skills.

programs.name: BA Digital Culture
programs.description: The BA Digital Culture program at Tilburg University explores the impact of digital technologies on society, culture, and the arts. The program combines theoretical insights with practical skills, preparing students for careers in media, cultural industries, and digital innovation.

programs.name: BSc Human Resource Studies: People Management
programs.description: The BSc Human Resource Studies: People Management at Tilburg University combines insights from psychology, sociology, economics, and management to understand and optimize human behavior in organizations. The program prepares students for careers in HR, organizational development, and consultancy.

programs.name: BSc International Sociology
programs.description: The BSc International Sociology at Tilburg University provides insights into global social issues, exploring topics such as inequality, migration, and cultural diversity. The program equips students with analytical and research skills to understand and address contemporary social challenges.

programs.name: BA Theology
programs.description: The BA Theology at Tilburg University explores religious traditions, beliefs, and ethical issues from a historical and contemporary perspective. The program prepares students for careers in academia, religious organizations, and social services.

programs.name: BSc Leisure Studies
programs.description: The BSc Leisure Studies at Tilburg University examines the role of leisure in society and its impact on individual well-being, economy, and culture. The program prepares students for careers in leisure management, tourism, and event planning.
